The capability to calculate the minimum cost for collecting chocolates of all types must be possessed by the system.The array of parameters, nums, should be sorted in ascending order to ensure that the system allows the user to perform multiple operations.Taking into account the cost of each operation, the minimum cost should be calculated by the system.The array of integers, nums, should be sorted in ascending order in order for the system to possess the ability to determine the types of chocolates that need to be collected.The calculation of the minimum cost should consider the cost of collecting each type of chocolate, while taking into account the parameters "nums" and "x".The final minimum cost should be furnished to the user by the system.